### Backend Wording API — use with Postman or VS Code REST Client
### Base URL (start backend on 8090 first)
@base = http://localhost:8090

### 1. GET translations (full matrix)
GET {{base}}/api/v1/translations

###

### 2. GET config (languages + versions)
GET {{base}}/api/v1/config

###

### 3. POST publish (example: publish FR)
POST {{base}}/api/v1/publish
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lang": "fr"
}

###

### 4. POST save draft (example body — adjust to your keys)
# Copy the full body from API.md §2 for a real save
POST {{base}}/api/v1/translations
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "translations": [
    {
      "key": "HOME",
      "values": {
        "fr": { "TITLE": "Accueil", "SUBTITLE": "Bienvenue" },
        "en": { "TITLE": "Home", "SUBTITLE": "Welcome" }
      },
      "isDraft": true
    }
  ]
}
